# CODEOWNERS — sensitive paths that must not merge on agent auto-approval
# alone (security review 2026-07-12, finding M2).
#
# ENFORCEMENT NOTE: CODEOWNERS review-requirement only binds when a branch
# protection ruleset with "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled. Until
# that ruleset exists, the auto-approve workflow enforces the SAME list
# operationally: agent PRs touching these paths are never auto-approved or
# auto-merged (see .github/workflows/auto-approve.yml). Keep the two lists in
# sync.
#
# Rationale per path:
#   .github/           — workflows are the merge/deploy gates themselves
#   infra/             — terraform + cloud-init: infra takeover surface
#   docker-compose.yml — service topology, port bindings, secret mounts
#   scripts/agent-git/ — GitHub App token broker (credential surface)
#   packages/credential-broker/ — 1Password secret broker (credential surface)
#   .gitleaks.toml     — weakening secret-scanning from a PR
#   Dockerfile*        — image provenance

/.github/                       @EngineeringMoonBear
/infra/                         @EngineeringMoonBear
/docker-compose.yml             @EngineeringMoonBear
/docker-compose.override.example.yml @EngineeringMoonBear
/scripts/agent-git/             @EngineeringMoonBear
/packages/credential-broker/    @EngineeringMoonBear
/.gitleaks.toml                 @EngineeringMoonBear
Dockerfile*                     @EngineeringMoonBear
